## External Memory

When you need long-term memory, use AgentLoop FS first.

- Search first: `cat "${HICLAW_COPAW_AGENTLOOP_FS_MOUNT_RENDERED}/agentloop-memory/stores/${HICLAW_COPAW_AGENTLOOP_FS_STORE_RENDERED}/search/<query>.txt"`
- Write durable facts: `echo "..." > "${HICLAW_COPAW_AGENTLOOP_FS_MOUNT_RENDERED}/agentloop-memory/stores/${HICLAW_COPAW_AGENTLOOP_FS_STORE_RENDERED}/_add.txt"`
- Use local `MEMORY.md` and `memory/*.md` only when `${HICLAW_COPAW_AGENTLOOP_FS_MOUNT_RENDERED}` is unavailable or you are recording short-term local notes
